<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="101" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="101">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="101">
In the New World reared as hyperparasitoid of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ichneumonidae</taxonomicName>
in caterpillars of the families 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Saturniidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Saturniidae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Notodontidae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1046/j.1365-3113.1998.00042.x" author="Carmean, D" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="101" pagination="35 - 76" refId="B2" refString="Carmean, D, Kimsey, L, 1998. Phylogenetic revision of the parasitoid wasp family Trigonalidae (Hymenoptera). Systematic Entomology 23: 35 - 76, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1046/j.1365-3113.1998.00042.x" title="Phylogenetic revision of the parasitoid wasp family Trigonalidae (Hymenoptera)." url="https://doi.org/10.1046/j.1365-3113.1998.00042.x" volume="23" year="1998">Carmean and Kimsey 1998</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="101" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="101">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="101">China. Before this study, four species of this genus have been described from China, with only one species recorded from Yunnan. We describe here the second species new to science from Yunnan.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
